15#define _QJS_PROP_OPTIONAL
16#define _QJS_PROP_REQUIRED REQUIRED
17
18#define _QJS_PROP_IMPL(TYPE, NAME, DEFAULT, ...) \
19 public: \
20 Q_SIGNAL void on_##NAME##_changed(); \
21 QJS_Prop<TYPE> JS_F(NAME){ [this]() { on_##NAME##_changed(); }, TYPE{ DEFAULT } }; \
22 Q_PROPERTY(TYPE NAME MEMBER JS_F(NAME) NOTIFY on_##NAME##_changed __VA_ARGS__)

24// ========================================================================================================
25//
26// QJsonStruct Public APIS
27//
28// ========================================================================================================
29
30template<typename T>
31struct QJS_Prop
32{
33 private:
34 T &set(T v)
35 {
36 if (value == v)
37 return value;
38 value = v;
39 pRealValue.markDirty();
40 onChanged();
41 return value;
42 }
43
44 public:
45 // clang-format off
46 T* operator->() { return &value; }
47 const T* operator->() const { return &value; }
48
49// T& operator()() { return value; }
50// const T& operator()() const { return value; }
51
52 T& operator*() { return value; }
53 const T& operator*() const { return value; }
54
55 operator T() { return value; }
56 operator const T() const { return value; }
57
58 T & operator=(const T& f) { return set(f); }
59 T & operator=(const QJS_Prop<T>& f) { return set(f.value); }
60
61 QJS_Prop<T> &operator++() { value++; return *this; }
62 QJS_Prop<T> &operator--() { value--; return *this; }
63
64 friend bool operator==(const QJS_Prop<T>& left, const T &right) { return left.value == right ; }
65 friend bool operator!=(const QJS_Prop<T>& left, const T &right) { return !(left.value == right); }
66
67 template<typename Y> void operator<<(const Y &another) { value << another; }
68 template<typename Y> void operator>>(const Y &another) { value >> another; }
69 template<typename V> T operator+=(const V &v) { return value += v; }
70 template<typename V> T operator-=(const V &v) { return value -= v; }
71 template<typename V> T operator*=(const V &v) { return value *= v; }
72 template<typename V> T operator/=(const V &v) { return value /= v; }
73 template<typename V> T operator&=(const V &v) { return value &= v; }
74 template<typename V> T operator%=(const V &v) { return value %= v; }
75
76 // JSON Serialization and Deserialization
77 QJsonValue toJson() const { return JsonStructHelper::Serialize(value); }
78 void loadJson(const QJsonValue &val) { JsonStructHelper::Deserialize(value, val); }
79 // clang-format on
80
81 private:
82 T value;
83 const T defaultValue;
84 QProperty<T> pRealValue{ [this]() { return value; } };
85 std::function<void(void)> onChanged;
86
87 public:
88 typedef T content_type;
89 QJS_Prop(std::function<void(void)> callback, const T &val) : value(val), defaultValue(val), onChanged(callback){};
90 virtual ~QJS_Prop() = default;
91
92 bool isDefault() const
93 {
94 return value == defaultValue;
95 }
96
97 QPropertyChangeHandler<std::function<void()>> RBindTo(QObject *target, const char *target_prop)
98 {
99 target->setProperty(target_prop, pRealValue.value());
100 return pRealValue.onValueChanged(std::function{ [=]() { target->setProperty(target_prop, pRealValue.value()); } });
101 }
102
103 template<typename TSender, typename Func>
104 inline void WBindTo(const TSender *target, const char *target_prop, Func target_slot)
105 {
106 static_assert(std::is_base_of_v<QObject, TSender>, "Wrong Usage");
107 QObject::connect(target, target_slot, [=]() { *this = ((QObject *) target)->property(target_prop).value<T>(); });
108 }
109};

111#define QJS_PROP(TYPE, NAME, ...) _QJS_PROP_IMPL(TYPE, NAME, TYPE{}, __VA_ARGS__)
112#define QJS_PROP_D(TYPE, NAME, DEFAULT, ...) _QJS_PROP_IMPL(TYPE, NAME, DEFAULT, __VA_ARGS__)

114#define QJS_FUNCTION_DEFAULT_CONSTRUCTOR(CLASS, ...) \
115 CLASS(){}; \
116 virtual ~CLASS(){};
117
118#define __QJS_CTOR_B(base) base()
119#define __QJS_CTOR_F(name)
120
121#define QJS_FUNCTION(CLASS, ...) \
122 public: \
123 QJS_FUNCTION_DEFAULT_CONSTRUCTOR(CLASS, __VA_ARGS__) \
124 QJS_FUNC_COPY(CLASS, __VA_ARGS__); \
125 QJS_FUNC_JSON(CLASS, __VA_ARGS__); \
126 QJS_FUNC_COMP(CLASS, __VA_ARGS__);
127
128#define QJS_FUNCTION_NODCTOR(CLASS, ...) \
129 public: \
130 QJS_FUNC_COPY(CLASS, __VA_ARGS__); \
131 QJS_FUNC_JSON(CLASS, __VA_ARGS__); \
132 QJS_FUNC_COMP(CLASS, __VA_ARGS__);

134#define QJS_RBINDING(sprop, target, tprop) property_bindings.push_back(sprop.RBindTo(target, tprop));
135#define QJS_WBINDING(sprop, target, tprop, tslot) sprop.WBindTo(target, tprop, tslot);
136
137#define QJS_RWBINDING(source_prop, target, target_prop, target_slot) \
138 QJS_RBINDING(source_prop, target, target_prop); \
139 QJS_WBINDING(source_prop, target, target_prop, target_slot);

141#define QJS_BINDING_CLEAR property_bindings.clear();
